IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. SIMPLE-FILE-MOVER.
AUTHOR. SIMON MIKKELSEN.

* This program moves files from one location to another.
* It takes user input for source and destination paths.
* It is designed to be overly complex and verbose.
* The program uses unnecessary variables and functions.
* It is written in a very precise and slightly angry style.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
CONFIGURATION SECTION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'INPUT.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'OUTPUT.DAT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE.
01  INPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(100).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-SOURCE-PATH PIC X(100).
01  WS-DEST-PATH PIC X(100).
01  WS-USER-INPUT PIC X(100).
01  WS-TEMP-VAR PIC X(100).
01  WS-LOTR-VAR PIC X(100).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PARA.
    DISPLAY 'Enter source path: '.
    ACCEPT WS-SOURCE-PATH.
    MOVE WS-SOURCE-PATH TO WS-USER-INPUT.
    PERFORM VALIDATE-INPUT.

    DISPLAY 'Enter destination path: '.
    ACCEPT WS-DEST-PATH.
    MOVE WS-DEST-PATH TO WS-USER-INPUT.
    PERFORM VALIDATE-INPUT.

    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE.
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE.

    PERFORM MOVE-FILES.

    CLOSE INPUT-FILE.
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE.

    DISPLAY 'File move completed.'.
    STOP RUN.

VALIDATE-INPUT.
    IF WS-USER-INPUT = SPACES
     DISPLAY 'Invalid input, try again.'
     STOP RUN
    END-IF.

MOVE-FILES.
    PERFORM UNTIL EOF
     READ INPUT-FILE INTO INPUT-RECORD
         AT END
          MOVE 'YES' TO EOF
     END-READ
     WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD FROM INPUT-RECORD
    END-PERFORM.

EOF SECTION.
01  EOF PIC X VALUE 'NO'.

